texts.text: So about this trial...
Sending us to a department store on a weekend is one thing...
But this seems pretty serious...
>You all look up at the building...
>And see that something is very wrong with it...
Yo, I doubt we're gonna get any sort of welcome wagon here.
We're almost certainly going to be attacked by demons instead.
But we'll just have to walk into their ambush.
>You enter the building.
>But despite being the weekend, there appears to be nobody else inside.
Well, nothing unexpected so far.
Somewhere that's normally packed is completely dead.
Now we know that whatever's going on outside is also going on inside.
Perfect! That just means we're allowed to go all out in here, right?
I kind of like this.
There aren't many places where I can shoot a gun as much as I like.
I don't have to worry about hitting anybody else.
Speak for yourself.
I like this too.
A department store that doesn't seem quite right...
We could become stuck and get attacked by zombies!
It's like something straight out of a horror film!
How can any of you be excited by this?! Seriously?!
Haha. Yo, it ain't all bad I guess. At least they're motivated.
But it's so quiet.
Yes, it is. Demons don't appear to be waiting to ambush us either.
Yeah, and this trial might actually be easier than we thought, you know?
And it said to meet it on top of the roof, right?
Let's hurry and get this all over with.

The elevator should be...
Aha, over there!
>Ririn runs ahead towards the elevator.
>But the buttons appear to be unresponsive...
Yo, Ririn, what's up?
Guys, how many floors does this building have...?

Fifty or sixty...
It's pretty tall.
And has one of the best views around here.
Arrgh!
Anyone else getting a stomach ache all of a sudden?
I don't think I can keep going with you guys.
So I'm gonna call it a day and...!
You're gonna have to do better than that!
I guess these are your true colors.
Yeah,  so what?! I really don't like it here!!
Yo, what's gotten into y'all?
For now, just press the button for the top floor and...
Oh...
>Megakin makes a terrible realization.
Yo, this trial's gonna be worse than we thought.
Just try to stay calm, y'all.
The elevator's getting' no power.
*Pant*
>The Liberators resort to climbing the stairs outside the building.
I'm so tired...!!

*Pant*
Yo, we don't have a choice.
No elevator means we gotta use the stairs...
Okay, fine... But why do these stairs have to be outside in the sun...?!
Again, we don't have any other choice.
For some reason, the stairs inside are all being blocked off by fire doors.
What's the point of doing that?!
Is this "trial" about enduring all this heat and pain?!
I'm done.
I can keep going.
Hang in there, [sys user_name]!
This may be a tough test, but we're all more than strong enough!
Let's just keep doing our best to overcome it!
Why do I get the feeling that you're liking this now...?
You don't have to push yourself like that, [sys user_name]...
Man, this heat's gonna wring me dry.
But I guess it is a good workout.
I didn't expect to hear that from you, Vince.
I was always under the impression that you hated exercise.
Vince is probably one of those people that never gains weight.
Dunno about that. To be fair, I didn't exactly live a healthy life when I was still with the Acolytes either.
But something about this conversation really bugs me for some reason.
That's because we're bad guys, Vince.
Normal conversations like this aren't good for us.
That explains it.
Okay?
Yo, enough chit chat. Who knows what else this trial's gonna throw at us?
Also, check out that door.
Looks like we can go back in through here.
But stay frosty, y'all. We ain't got no idea what's waitin' for us inside.
Let's go!
We don't have a choice!
Here we go!
>You enter through the door...
>Then...
Ah, you are here...
Shaddai?!
What are you doing here...?
Yo, this ain't a coincidence, it is...?
Correct.
Liberators, you will now be given your first trial.
>Angels appear as if they were awaiting Shaddai's signal!
>A whole army of them is soon mustered.
H-How many are there...?!
You are to face us.
You must defeat us if you wish to proceed!
We shall see if you can fell all of them, Liberators.
This is my challenge to you.
